# Kaixu SuperIDE — Fortune 500 Upgrade List

Everything below is required to go from "production-capable startup IDE" to "Fortune 500 / enterprise-ready."
Roughly 2–3 weeks of build work total.

---

## 1. Tests + CI Pipeline

**Why:** No test files exist. Procurement and enterprise buyers require evidence of automated testing.

Build:
- Unit tests for every Netlify function (auth, billing, quota, RBAC, invites)
- Integration tests: full signup → invite → workspace → AI call flow
- Tenant isolation tests: prove org A cannot read org B data
- Permission test suite: verify every role (owner/admin/editor/viewer) is enforced
- GitHub Actions workflow: lint → test → deploy on push to main
- Tools: Jest (unit), Supertest (HTTP integration), Playwright (E2E optional)

Files to create:
- tests/auth.test.js
- tests/billing.test.js
- tests/rbac.test.js
- tests/tenant-isolation.test.js
- tests/quota.test.js
- .github/workflows/ci.yml

